    "The need for such data, including for specific vocal techniques like growls and rough voice (Gómez et al., 2018), motivated self-supervised systems incorporating DDSP like NANSY++ (Choi H.-S. et al., 2023), which supported high-quality resynthesis with a fraction of the OpenCPOP dataset (Wang et al., 2022).",
    "Wu D.-Y. et al. (2022) also found that the differentiable vocoder SawSing performed well in resource-limited training.",
